slides.content:
Add an `else` clause to run code when the condition is FALSE.

```r
if (condition) {
  # runs if TRUE
} else {
  # runs if FALSE
}
```

Note: In R, the `else` must be on the same line as the closing brace of the `if` block, or you can use curly braces for clarity.

Chain multiple conditions using `else if`:

```r
if (condition1) {
  # first
} else if (condition2) {
  # second
} else {
  # none of the above
}
```

slides.codeSnippet:
score <- 85
if (score >= 90) {
  grade <- 'A'
} else if (score >= 80) {
  grade <- 'B'
} else if (score >= 70) {
  grade <- 'C'
} else {
  grade <- 'F'
}
print(grade)

